    <p>WELLINGTON • South Africa have reaf­firmed their com­mit­ment to the Rugby Cham­pi­onship for the next decade, the or­gan­is­ers San­zaar said yes­ter­day, bring­ing an end to spec­u­la­tion the world cham­pi­ons may look to join Europe’s Six Na­tions.</p>
    <p>San­zaar also said the four-na­tion al­liance, which also in­cludes New Zealand, Aus­tralia and Ar­gentina, would be re­struc­tured and a “re­vised” 10-year strate­gic plan would in­clude “fu­ture growth and ex­pan­sion” for the tour­na­ment.</p>


